HEADWORD: Enseal
<hw>En*seal"</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧n*s⟦emac⟧l")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
impress with a seal; to mark as with a seal; hence, to ratify.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This deed I do <qex>enseal</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Piers
Plowman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enseam</ent>⟦br⟧
